history.content: Yes, that's right - it makes more sense to go for a discussion with more open seats/less people on the waitlist (8 a.m./9 a.m. or 5 p..m. are your best bets), because your lecture waitlist position is immaterial vs. discussion -  you need to get into a discussion (and for there to be at least one open spot in lecture) to get into the class.

Hi, during phase 1 I waitlisted for CS161 and am currently number 56 on the waitlist. However, I just realized that I made the mistake of waitlisting for a discussion section that only has 2 spots available. As I understand it, the discussion section needs to be open to get into the class at all. Since the discussion section is nearly full, should I switch to one of the discussion sections that has more room? I think this would require me to lose my spot on the waitlist and move to the end, but maybe this doesn't matter since discussion space determines whether you can get in anyway?
history.subject: On waitlist for nearly full 161 discussion section, should I switch?
